{"questionId":"9075108","questionHtml":"<p>Identify the terms in the formula.</p>\n<p><em>u′</em> =&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{u - v}}{{1 - \\frac{{uv}}{{{c^2}}}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>u</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mi>v</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>u</mi>\n          <mi>v</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <msup>\n              <mi>c</mi>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </msup>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>u</em> and <em>v</em> are velocities with respect to the same frame of reference/Earth <em><strong>AND</strong> u′</em> the relative velocity</p>\n<p><em>Accept 0.4c and 0.6c for u and v</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9075108","referenceCode":"17N.3.SL.TZ0.5c","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Identify the terms in the formula. u′ = u − v 1 − u v c 2","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity (Core topics)","A.2 – Lorentz transformations","Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity (Core topics)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}